main event: Unidentified flying objects were sighted over Cheyenne, Wyoming on multiple occasions in September 1965.
interesting points: The objects included a large elliptical-shaped object with red and green lights that hovered before accelerating away., Several military personnel were involved in observing the sightings., The objects were reported to be bright and white, resembling the size of a silver dollar at arm's length., The visual observations were confirmed by radar technology and a Geodetic Survey Team., The conditions of the sightings were clear and calm with no sound reported from the objects.
sighted object: various unidentified flying objects including a large elliptical-shaped object
witness description: military personnel and civilians observing the objects with binoculars
